raw:
The image you've provided appears to be a screenshot of an online survey or questionnaire. To address the validation feedback, here are the actions that need to be taken for each question:

1. For "trust_coverage":
   - Select the radio button corresponding to your level of trust in Olympic coverage.
2. For "mood_impact":
   - Select the radio button corresponding to how positively the Olympics affected your day-to-day mood.
3. For "age":
   - Enter your age in the text box provided, ensuring it is within the acceptable range of 18 to 99.
4. For "follow_by_age":
   - Select the option that best describes how closely you followed the most recent Winter Olympics compared with people in your age group.
5. For "employment_status":
   - Select the option that corresponds to your current employment status.
6. For "watch_time":
   - Use the slider input to set the amount of time spent daily on Olympics content during the Olympics period, ensuring it is within the acceptable range of 1 to 10 hours.
7. For "attention_text_mid":
   - Select the option that best describes how closely you followed the Olympics in the middle of your day-to-day life.
8. For "country_satisfaction":
   - Use the slider input to rate your satisfaction with your country's Olympic performance, ensuring it is within the acceptable range of 1 to 10.
9. For "future_interest":
   - Select the option that best describes how likely you are to follow the next Olympics.
10. For "favorite_moment":
    - Enter a brief description of one memorable Olympic moment for you in the text box provided.

After completing these actions, you can then click on the "Next" button at the bottom right corner of the image to proceed to the next page of the survey.

After completing these actions, click on the "Next" button at the bottom right corner of the image to proceed to the next page of the survey.
